snippet: Kaleena Mosqueda-Lewis, the freshman guard from Anaheim Hills, Calif., came off the bench to score 19 points and lead Connecticut to the Big East title.
abstract: Connecticut defeats Notre Dame, 63-54, to win the Big East women's college basketball tournament.
lead_paragraph: Kaleena Mosqueda-Lewis, the freshman guard from Anaheim Hills, Calif., came off the bench to score 19 points and lead Connecticut to the Big East title.

headline.seo: Connecticut Captures Big East Women’s Title
headline.main: A Visitor in Own Building, UConn Puts Up Its Feet
headline.print_headline: A Visitor in Own Building, UConn Puts Up Its Feet
